All Implemented Interfaces:
Observable
public class ResourceCard extends PlayableCard
Implementation of ResourceCard for Model A type of Card that can be placed without conditions. Its corners can be empty or hold a resource. On the backSide there is always a KingdomResource in the center, making it impossible to cover. Placing a ResourceCard can earn the player up to 1 point.

      Constructor Method with x and y coordinates. USE THIS ONLY if you need to specify the Card's coordinates.
      Parameters:
      frontSide - : CardSide to be used as the front side of the Card
      backSide - : CardSide to be used as the front side of the Card
      isFrontFacing - : boolean to specify which side of the Card is visible ( True -> front, False -> back )
      id - : unique identifier for the specific Card
      x - : horizontal coordinate for the Card's position on the table (null if not placed)
      y - : vertical coordinate for the Card's position on the table (null if not placed)
      permanentResource - : KingdomResource shown on the back side of the Card
      earnedPoints - : number of points obtained for placing the card
      frontImage - : a String containing the Description of the Objective, displayed in the GUI.
      backImage - : a String containing the Description of the Objective, displayed in the GUI.
